The paper deals with the problem of zero-shot learning, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves the use of semantic embeddings and visual features, which are also relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the experiments are conducted on image datasets, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM).
